description.narrative: Basic service providers at the national and subnational level have increased capacity to develop and prioritize equity-focused, evidence-based policies and budgets and are better able to respond to emergencies., which contributes to Access To Justice, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 girls and boys are better protected from violence, abuse and exploitation

description.narrative: In partnership with government institutions, UNICEF continued to implement its programme to end violence against children, improve the justice system for children in contact with the law and develop a coordinated and accountable child protection system in Libya, in line with Libya's international and regional human rights obligations and best practices. UNICEF particularly focused on providing support to children in schools and communities, children without appropriate care and children in conflict with the law. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/08/2020
